## Comment 4 — Empty service name in runGcloudProxy
**Severity**: approve-blocker
**File**: cmd/adkgo/internal/deploy/agentengine/agentengine.go:303
**Request**: Handle the case where `f.agentEngine.name` is empty. You should either validate that the user passed the `--name` flag, default it, or extract the underlying service name from the created Reasoning Engine.
**Why**: If the user omits the optional `--name` flag, the deploy step will succeed but the local proxy step will execute `gcloud run services proxy ""` which immediately fails due to an empty service name.

## Comment 5 — Missing required flag validation
**Severity**: nice-to-have
